        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 6 at 3:30AM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 330 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles north of Sterlington to over
Dubberly, or extending from 15 miles north of Swartz to 7 miles
southeast of Minden, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Monroe, Ruston, Claiborne, Minden, West Monroe, Grambling,
Brownsville-Bawcomville, Brownsville-Bawcom, Swartz, Farmerville,
Arcadia, Bernice, Sterlington, Ringgold, Sibley, Gibsland,
Doyline, Dubberly, Dixie Inn and Heflin.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional
information and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
